

css bg properties - used to define the bg effects for elements


css background elements : 

*background-color {
ex :  background-color: colorName;

colorName - valid color name : "red";
         -hex value
         -rgb value 
};

*background-image {
  an image set as a background of an element
  
  ex :  background-image: url("paper.gif");

  by default - the img repeats  both horizontally and vertically.
};

*background-repeat{
 modul in care sa se afiseze imaginea in pagina
};

*background-attachment{
specify if the img should be fixex - meaning that the img wont scroll with the rest of the page
};

*background-position{
pozitia imaginii
};

*background- origin {
originea 
};

CSS Syntax

background: bg-color bg-image position/bg-size bg-repeat 
bg-origin bg-clip bg-attachment initial|inherit;